{
  "stem": "26672.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My body shakes, not of nervousness, but of remembering what it was like.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I can't describe it to you, or even how much we put in the video, what it was really like.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I recently thought, how come people can deny that this ever existed when we've got a proof of myself and others-- not many others still after 50, 55 years-- still people deny.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The only thing I can think of is that it's impossible for them to imagine that one human being could do this to another.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Even animals to one another don't do this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And after all, we are human beings, and especially talking about a German nation, educated nation, that they could instill such hatred.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I must tell you that some of the Germans weren't as bad as some of the Poles, or the Ukrainians, that went over, or the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Everybody had to show that they can do better.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that is something that we can't pass on to others, because each one has his own story.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And if people didn't go through what I went through, maybe in different ways, there were some people who suffered in Siberia.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it still wasn't the same thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were beaten.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were hard labored.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But to do the sort of thing, to take a child by the head, and shoot it, or knock it against the wall, how can one human being do that?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we think of it, it's not really tears.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It brings more back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'd like to think that my sisters didn't go through that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At least they died, death was quick, less painful.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think of [INAUDIBLE], that I was pushed, eventually, had the sense of crying that I was a man.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
